parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel makes an abnormal ticking or screeching sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ignition shuts down without warning
the vehicle crashes
the airbags fail to deploy
the warning indicators on the instrument panel illuminate
the engine fails to start
and the cruise control cuts out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the anti-theft warning light illuminates
and the ignition switch needs to be reprogrammed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: The brake lights stay on continuously while driving
the brake lights fail to work at all
and the brake light warning indicator illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the passenger presence sensor defaults
and the airbag system fails to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can make it difficult to control the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering fails to work
the steering wheel locks in the opposite direction
and the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate or decelerate, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control cuts out
the brake lights stay on
and the vehicle suddenly accelerates or decelerates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission system can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission cylinder is off
the transmission fails to engage
and the vehicle suddenly loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Warning Light Illumination and Failure to Deploy
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the "Service Airbag" message appears on the screen
the passenger airbag warning light stays on
and the airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger seat occupancy sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the airbag warning light illuminating and potentially preventing the airbags from deploying in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the "Service Airbag" message appears on the screen
and the passenger airbag warning light stays on.
